ORIGINAL DESIGNS AND CONCEPTS
================================================================================

The following designs, protocols, and interaction paradigms were originated
by the Coffee CLI project. The source code that implements them is governed
by the AGPL-3.0 license; the underlying ideas are documented here so that
downstream forks and reimplementations can credit prior art appropriately.

  1. Gambit — A floating-island input surface that routes a single keyboard
     stream to multiple terminal sessions.

  2. Pitch — Per-task input dispatch from a kanban-style TODO board
     directly into a target terminal session: a single click composes
     a task's title and description into the input stream of a chosen
     AI agent's terminal pane. Implementation in src-ui/src/components/
     right/TaskBoard.tsx (sendToAgent).

  3. Coffee-CLI MCP — A multi-agent coordination protocol that lets AI
     agents running in separate terminal panes observe, signal, and
     mutually invoke each other through a Model Context Protocol (MCP)
     server hosted by the Coffee CLI desktop app. Implementation under
     src/mcp_server.rs.

  4. Sentinel Protocol — A supervisory mechanism that monitors and arbitrates
     multi-agent activity across terminal sessions.

  5. VibeID — A 16-archetype personality framework derived from a user's
     behavioral telemetry while operating AI coding agents. The framework,
     the four-axis derivation method, the coined noun **Vibetype**
     (a portmanteau of "vibe" + "archetype" used to label each test
     result), and all 16 individual Vibetype names and write-ups, are
     claimed as original works. The terms "VibeCoding" (popularized by
     Andrej Karpathy) and "Claw" are NOT original to this project and
     are not claimed.

These innovations are protected as original expression under copyright law
and, where applicable, as common-law trademarks. See TRADEMARKS.md for the
brand and naming policy.

